## Appendix 6 - Alternative method: logistic regression

Another set of models was constructed, this time switching the method to logistic regression with generalized linear models instead of using linear probability models. Since the dependent variable is dichotomous, a logit model might be fit to estimate coefficients that imply probabilities that fall inside of the unit interval, in this case between 0 and 1. As one can see from tables 5 and 6, the coefficients of interest remain in the same direction as the linear probability models.

```{r echo=FALSE, results="asis"}
